<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1238#">Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1238</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_63.2-1238"/><heading><desig>§ 63.2-1238.</desig><title>Forwarding of petition; when investigation and report not required</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Upon the filing of the petition, the circuit court shall forward a copy of the petition and all exhibits thereto to the Commissioner and to the local director where the petitioners reside or resided at the time of filing the petition, or had legal residence at the time of the filing of the petition. However, in cases where a licensed child-placing agency has completed a home study, the petition and all exhibits shall be forwarded to the licensed child-placing agency.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> In parental placement adoptions where consent has been properly executed, no investigation and report pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 63.2-1208"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1208">§ 63.2-1208<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1208#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> is required. However, the circuit court may order a thorough investigation of the matter and report in which case the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 63.2-1208"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1208">§ 63.2-1208<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1208#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> shall apply.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 63-349; 1954, c. 489; 1956, c. 489; 1956, c. 187; 1962, c. 603; 1964, c. 429; 1968, cc. 346, 578, § 63.1-223; 1974, cc. 26, 493, 507; 1975, c. 364; 1978, c. 730; 1980, c. 740; 1982, c. 115; 1988, cc. 579, 599, 882; <citation normalizedCite="1989 VA CH 647"><content><span normalizedCite="1989 Va. Ch. 647">1989, c. 647<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1989#000647#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1992 VA CH 607"><content><span normalizedCite="1992 Va. Ch. 607">1992, c. 607<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1992#000607#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1993 VA CH 553"><content><span normalizedCite="1993 Va. Ch. 553">1993, c. 553<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1993#000553#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 772"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 772">1995, cc. 772<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000772#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 826"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 826">826<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000826#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 830"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 830">2000, c. 830<l